definition: US Food and Drug Administration authority (FDA)
pinyin: shi2 wu4 ji2 yao4 pin3 guan3 li3 ju2

sentences.english: The glycemic index ranks foods based on how much they raise blood sugar.
sentences.chinese: 血糖指数衡量食物提升血糖的速度。

sentences.english: You can get the norwalk virus from hand to mouth activity or from contaminated food.
sentences.chinese: 你可以得到手诺瓦克病毒污染的食物或活动口。

sentences.english: Eat fat food less, no-noSmokeWine, answer to often maintain defecate unobstructed .
sentences.chinese: 少吃油腻食物，禁忌烟酒，并应经常保持大便通畅。

sentences.english: In some extend, I am not a hypercritical person about food.
sentences.chinese: 在某种程度上，我对于食物是一点都不挑剔的。

sentences.english: He and his family will also be getting food from the charity.
sentences.chinese: 他和他的家人也将通过慈善组织获得食物。

sentences.english: In one case it began stretching its neck just before the food was delivered.
sentences.chinese: 有一次它在食物送到之前就拉长了脖子。

sentences.english: She gave us food and clothes and asked for nothing in return.
sentences.chinese: 她给了我们食物和衣服，没求任何回报。

sentences.english: If pregnant, take an iron supplement, as recommended by an obstetrician or other health care provider.
sentences.chinese: 如怀孕，要在妇产医生的指导下食用补铁的食物。

sentences.english: Why are GM foods potentially allergenic?
sentences.chinese: 为什么转基因食物可能会引起过敏？

sentences.english: That mixture is enough to move his jeep; however, whenever the car moves, it exhales food smell.
sentences.chinese: 当车子开动时，总是会散发出食物的味道。

sentences.english: Results Food-poisoning accidents happen more frequently in the third quarter.
sentences.chinese: 结果食物中毒事故第三季度高发。

sentences.english: Sensing food, a roach peers into a two-foot-tall pitcher plant.
sentences.chinese: 发现食物，一只蟑螂仔细观察着两英尺高的猪笼草。

sentences.english: Reduce edible salt bloats, smoke, barbecue food.
sentences.chinese: 减少食用盐腌，烟熏，烧烤的食物。

sentences.english: Food and water ran short, power blacked out.
sentences.chinese: 食物和水越来越少，电力也被切断了。

sentences.english: These camp robbers hae become habituated to campers as a food source.
sentences.chinese: 这些营地掠夺者已经惯于将野营者作为一种食物来源。

definition: to eat/to consume/to eat at (a cafeteria etc)/to eradicate/to destroy/to absorb/to suffer/to stammer (Taiwan pr. for this sense is [ji2])
